OL,6,FPenny Bell's mum, Rosemary, was
OL,7,Fdiagnosed with mixed dementia in
OL,8,F2016. While Penny was able to support
OL,9,Fher mum at home for several years, it
OL,10,Feventually became apparent that it
OL,11,Fwas becoming unsafe for Rosemary to
OL,12,Flive independently, and it was time
OL,13,Ffor her to move into a care home.
OL,15,F"There was no further support offered
OL,16,Fafter Mum was told she had mixed
OL,17,Fdementia. At the time, in 2016, her
OL,18,FGP was able to make the diagnosis, so
OL,19,Fwe were never referred to a memory
OL,20,Fclinic.
OL,3,C'We were left with no support after
OL,4,Cmy mum was diagnosed with dementia'
